spec.rls:
Both new tables: ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY. Writes from cron/settings API go through service_role (bypasses RLS) — but policies still required by project rule "RLS on every table".

curator_notification_settings:
  -- curator reads/writes only own row; admins read all (for support)
  DROP POLICY IF EXISTS cns_select_own ON curator_notification_settings;
  CREATE POLICY cns_select_own ON curator_notification_settings FOR SELECT
    USING (curator_id = auth.uid() OR is_admin());
  DROP POLICY IF EXISTS cns_upsert_own ON curator_notification_settings;
  CREATE POLICY cns_insert_own ON curator_notification_settings FOR INSERT
    WITH CHECK (curator_id = auth.uid() OR is_admin());
  CREATE POLICY cns_update_own ON curator_notification_settings FOR UPDATE
    USING (curator_id = auth.uid() OR is_admin())
    WITH CHECK (curator_id = auth.uid() OR is_admin());

curator_inactivity_alerts (internal dedup ledger — no client access needed):
  DROP POLICY IF EXISTS cia_admin_only ON curator_inactivity_alerts;
  CREATE POLICY cia_select_admin ON curator_inactivity_alerts FOR SELECT
    USING (curator_id = auth.uid() OR is_admin());
  -- no INSERT/UPDATE policy for anon/authed → only service_role (cron) writes.

Reuse existing is_admin() (defined in 20260501130000_v3_roles_hierarchy.sql). Note: the MiniApp settings API uses service_role via requireCuratorViaInitData, so it enforces "own row" in CODE (curator_id := authed userId), mirroring the existing curator-auth pattern; RLS is the second line of defense.

curator_student_focus — RLS ENABLED (mandatory). Panel reaches it via service_role (bypasses RLS), so these policies are a defense-in-depth backstop for any future direct supabase-js/auth access (e.g. if focus is ever surfaced in /m/* miniapp).

ALTER TABLE public.curator_student_focus ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Куратор видит/правит только свои фокус-записи
CREATE POLICY csf_curator_select ON public.curator_student_focus
  FOR SELECT TO authenticated
  USING ( curator_id = auth.uid() );
CREATE POLICY csf_curator_write ON public.curator_student_focus
  FOR ALL TO authenticated
  USING ( curator_id = auth.uid() )
  WITH CHECK ( curator_id = auth.uid() );

-- Админы/супер-админы — полный доступ (через подзапрос роли)
CREATE POLICY csf_admin_all ON public.curator_student_focus
  FOR ALL TO authenticated
  USING ( EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.profiles p WHERE p.id = auth.uid() AND p.role IN ('admin','super_admin')) )
  WITH CHECK ( EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.profiles p WHERE p.id = auth.uid() AND p.role IN ('admin','super_admin')) );

GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON public.curator_student_focus TO authenticated;
GRANT ALL ON public.curator_student_focus TO service_role;

IMPORTANT — primary authorization is in the API layer, NOT RLS, because /panel uses service-role. Every focus/report/students route MUST re-check: if session.role==='curator' then constrain to curator_id===session.uid. Do not rely on RLS for the curator-scoping guarantee. Add a thin guard helper apps/web/src/lib/admin/scope.ts: isCuratorScope(session) and assertOwnsStudent(supabase, session, studentId).

spec.dataModel:
TWO migrations, both IF NOT EXISTS / idempotent, in supabase/migrations/.

=== Migration A: 20260621100000_v3_profile_rich_fields.sql ===
-- Текстовые поля богатого профиля (ввод ученика → React auto-escape на рендере)
ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS occupation     TEXT;  -- «чем занимается», <=160
ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS bio            TEXT;  -- «о себе», <=1000
ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS testimony      TEXT;  -- «как и когда пришёл к Богу», <=4000
ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS profile_links  JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]'::jsonb; -- [{label,url}], max 5
-- CHECK длины опциональны (валидируем в API), но добавим лёгкие гард-чеки:
ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD CONSTRAINT profiles_occupation_len CHECK (occupation IS NULL OR char_length(occupation) <= 160) NOT VALID;
ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD CONSTRAINT profiles_bio_len CHECK (bio IS NULL OR char_length(bio) <= 1000) NOT VALID;
ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD CONSTRAINT profiles_testimony_len CHECK (testimony IS NULL OR char_length(testimony) <= 4000) NOT VALID;
COMMENT ON COLUMN public.profiles.profile_links IS 'JSON-массив {label,url} ссылок профиля. http(s) только. Макс 5. Ввод ученика — экранировать на рендере.';

=== Migration B: 20260621100100_v3_profile_media.sql ===
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.profile_media (
  id           UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id      UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  kind         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (kind IN ('photo','audio','video','document')),
  storage_path TEXT NOT NULL,        -- путь в приватном бакете profile-media
  caption      TEXT,                 -- ввод ученика, <=300
  sort_order   INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_profile_media_user ON public.profile_media (user_id, sort_order);
ALTER TABLE public.profile_media ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
-- Доступ ТОЛЬКО через service_role API (в /m/* нет supabase-сессии). authenticated-политика — задел.
DROP POLICY IF EXISTS profile_media_select ON public.profile_media;
CREATE POLICY profile_media_select ON public.profile_media FOR SELECT TO authenticated USING (true);
-- Приватный бакет (как community-media): раздача через signed URL на сервере.
INSERT INTO storage.buckets (id, name, public, file_size_limit, allowed_mime_types)
VALUES ('profile-media','profile-media',FALSE,52428800,
  ARRAY['image/jpeg','image/png','image/webp','audio/mpeg','audio/mp4','audio/x-m4a','audio/webm','video/mp4','video/webm','application/pdf'])
ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;

WHY a table (not just columns): media is 0..N per user with caption+order → relational. Текстовые поля 1:1 → колонки на profiles. profile_links как JSONB (<=5, плоский, без сортировки/файлов) достаточно — отдельной таблицы не нужно. Деньги нигде не участвуют. После обеих миграций — регенерация types.ts (mcp__supabase generate_typescript_types) + tsc --noEmit (см. memory feedback_regen_types_after_migration).

MIGRATION: supabase/migrations/20260621120000_v3_gender_theme_pref.sql (follow project convention: timestamp_v3_name, IF NOT EXISTS, COMMENT ON COLUMN, RLS untouched).

Two columns on public.profiles:
  ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS gender TEXT;
  ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS theme_pref TEXT;
  -- constraints as NOT VALID-safe CHECKs added separately so re-run is safe:
  DO $$ BEGIN
    ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD CONSTRAINT profiles_gender_chk CHECK (gender IS NULL OR gender IN ('male','female'));
  EXCEPTION WHEN duplicate_object THEN NULL; END $$;
  DO $$ BEGIN
    ALTER TABLE public.profiles ADD CONSTRAINT profiles_theme_pref_chk CHECK (theme_pref IS NULL OR theme_pref IN ('light','dark','stars','pink'));
  EXCEPTION WHEN duplicate_object THEN NULL; END $$;
  COMMENT ON COLUMN public.profiles.gender IS 'Пол ученика, собирается ТОЛЬКО для выбора темы оформления (female → розовая по умолчанию). NULL = не указан. Не используется для логики курса.';
  COMMENT ON COLUMN public.profiles.theme_pref IS 'Явно выбранная пользователем тема MiniApp (light/dark/stars/pink). NULL = использовать дефолт по gender. Перекрывает localStorage при загрузке профиля.';

Rationale: gender is nullable TEXT (NOT an enum/NOT NOT-NULL) so onboarding can keep it optional and the church context is not forced into a binary. theme_pref is separate from gender so a user can deliberately pick a different theme than their gender default and we remember it. No money/INTEGER fields involved. After migration: regenerate types.ts (mcp__supabase generate_typescript_types) + tsc --noEmit per memory feedback_regen_types_after_migration.

EXISTING relevant columns (verified, profiles): id, full_name, contact_info, avatar_path, role, country_id, city_id, curator_id, is_protected, hidden_from_tracking, course_started_at, onboarding_done, streak_count, last_active_date, telegram_chat_id, can_skip_block_lock, is_whitelisted, lang. NO gender/theme today.

MIGRATION (one file, additive only, IF NOT EXISTS everywhere). File: supabase/migrations/20260622000000_v3_perf_indexes_and_summary.sql

A) Covering indexes for the UNION-ALL scans (each daily table grouped by user_id, block_id, date — currently no composite index):
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_cross_ubd ON student_block_daily_cross(user_id, block_id, submitted_date);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_prayer_ubd ON student_block_daily_prayer(user_id, block_id, prayed_date);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_recit_audio ON student_block_recitations(user_id, block_id, created_at) WHERE medium='audio' AND passed;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_recit_video ON student_block_recitations(user_id, block_id, created_at) WHERE medium='video_note' AND passed;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_trainer_ubd ON student_block_daily_trainer(user_id, block_id, trained_date);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_sla_video_passed ON student_location_attempts(user_id, location_id, created_at) WHERE medium='video_note' AND passed;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_sda_user_opened ON student_daily_activity(user_id, activity_date) WHERE opened;

B) New RPC closed_dates_filtered(p_user_ids uuid[]) RETURNS TABLE(user_id uuid, d date) — exact copy of closed_dates_all body but with WHERE user_id = ANY(p_user_ids) pushed into each UNION-ALL branch. SECURITY DEFINER, SET search_path='', REVOKE ALL FROM PUBLIC, GRANT EXECUTE TO service_role. closed_dates_all() stays for back-compat. Same for passed_blocks_filtered(p_user_ids uuid[]). Tracking already has the id list, so the scan is bounded to visible students.

C) (Optional, defer to L-effort) Materialized table student_progress_summary(user_id uuid PRIMARY KEY, blocks_passed int NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, closed_days int NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, last_closed_date date, updated_at timestamptz DEFAULT now()), refreshed by trigger/cron, so panel reads O(1). RLS ENABLE + policy USING(false) — service-role only. Do only if A+B insufficient.

No column drops, no destructive ops. After migration: regenerate packages/supabase/src/types + tsc --noEmit (per memory feedback_regen_types_after_migration).
